{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/osteoarthritis/background-information/prevalence/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"8696aed8-8dba-5a61-a12d-83015e11e6f3","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 9588c56a-846b-449f-bfea-a77400acee81 --><h2>How common is it?</h2><!-- end field 9588c56a-846b-449f-bfea-a77400acee81 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 7ece04d3-fa3d-4f22-8010-a77400acec16 --><!-- begin field f3f92a59-dad3-4d81-a092-a77400acee81 --><p><strong>Osteoarthritis is the most common joint disease worldwide, affecting an estimated 10% of men and 18% of women over 60 years of age </strong>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/osteoarthritis/references/\">Glyn-Jones, 2015</a>]<strong>.</strong></p><ul><li><strong>It is estimated that 8.75 million people aged over 45 years in the UK have sought treatment for osteoarthritis</strong> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/osteoarthritis/references/\">Arthritis Research UK, 2013</a>]. A population-based study of primary care data in England between 2000 and 2010 (total practice population of 94,955) found newly diagnosed cases of osteoarthritis occur in 9 per 1000 at-risk adults each year [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/osteoarthritis/references/\">Yu, 2015</a>].<ul><li><strong>The prevalence of osteoarthritis varies depending on the joint affected:</strong><ul><li>About 18% of the UK population aged over 45 years have sought treatment for osteoarthritis of the knee [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/osteoarthritis/references/\">Arthritis Research UK, 2013</a>].</li><li>About 8% of the UK population aged over 45 years have sought treatment for osteoarthritis of the hip [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/osteoarthritis/references/\">Arthritis Research UK, 2013</a>].</li><li>About 6% of the UK population aged over 45 years have sought treatment for osteoarthritis of the hand and wrist [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/osteoarthritis/references/\">Arthritis Research UK, 2013</a>], and it most commonly affects postmenopausal women [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/osteoarthritis/references/\">Anakwe, 2011</a>].</li><li>A population-based study of primary care data in England found the joint-specific incidence of osteoarthritis was 3.5 for the knee, 1.4 for the hip, and 1.3 for the hand [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/osteoarthritis/references/\">Yu, 2015</a>].</li></ul></li><li><strong>The risk of developing osteoarthritis increases with age.</strong><ul><li>A third of women and almost a quarter of men between 45 and 64 years of age have sought treatment for osteoarthritis. This rises to almost half of people aged 75 years and over [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/osteoarthritis/references/\">Arthritis Research UK, 2013</a>].</li><li>A population-based study of primary care data in England found the annual consultation incidence of osteoarthritis increased sharply between 45 and 64 years of age, peaking at 75–84 years of age [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/osteoarthritis/references/\">Yu, 2015</a>].</li></ul></li><li><strong>The prevalence of osteoarthritis is higher in women than men.</strong><ul><li>A third of women and almost a quarter of men between 45 and 64 years of age have sought treatment for osteoarthritis [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/osteoarthritis/references/\">Arthritis Research UK, 2013</a>].</li><li>The prevalence of symptomatic X-ray confirmed osteoarthritis is higher in women than men, especially after the age of 50 years and for hand and knee involvement [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/osteoarthritis/references/\">NICE, 2014</a>]. </li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field f3f92a59-dad3-4d81-a092-a77400acee81 --><!-- end item 7ece04d3-fa3d-4f22-8010-a77400acec16 -->","topic":{"id":"de61cfe3-a7fc-50bd-87eb-af7e90b20bfc","topicId":"c9866707-687c-4314-bff3-ae71e0d7e669","topicName":"Osteoarthritis","slug":"osteoarthritis","lastRevised":"Last revised in June 2018","chapters":[{"id":"9674ea7a-b052-5c2f-a0a1-336c67e0622a","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"aec2334e-8ee7-5d04-902e-c9a904550f17","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"6a895bdb-e3ce-53e5-a302-6bbca48a6e9f","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"5ae3cd70-eacb-5c4c-98f5-dace0da22472","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"2723ad88-c2c8-5b92-ac37-5d5af66e900a","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"3ffc0128-f379-5b16-bfbb-fe9c04753b07","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"740484d6-e553-5d2a-bcbf-22e4b61e30c8","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"2ab52642-cd7c-5b7d-a3c9-911580e1911c","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"3bb32b14-2fda-58fa-b09c-cd98270c7adb","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"35eeb6be-f0dd-5cde-a148-b87e5da25be5","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"3a253c38-1fe5-581e-8eff-eb2e5225d071","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"06733eae-d1c5-59d1-a725-266721a216af","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"3825aa8e-f0d5-5c9c-89b4-1898289f4fc9","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":